---
import SectionTitle from './SectionTitle.astro';
---

<section class="section-border flex items-center justify-center px-[16px] md:px-[40px] lg:px-[80px] py-[32px] md:py-[64px]">
  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row flex-1 max-w-[848px] items-start gap-[16px] md:gap-0 md:justify-between">
    <!-- Section Title (left) -->
    <div class="flex-1" data-scroll-reveal>
      <SectionTitle title="About Me" />
    </div>

    <!-- Content (right) -->
    <div class="flex w-full md:w-[632px] flex-col gap-[16px]" data-scroll-reveal>
      <p class="text-[24px] md:text-[28px] font-semibold leading-[32px] md:leading-[36px] tracking-[-1.7px] text-content-primary">
        My work sits at the intersection of business goals, user needs and technical constraints.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[16px] leading-[24px] text-content-primary">
        Over the past 3 years, I've worked on digital products spanning hospitality, SaaS, and marketing.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[16px] leading-[24px] text-content-primary">
        My design philosophy can be summed up in two words: curiosity and craft. Ask why things work the way they do, then make them better. For me, good design isn't just about clean screens or clever interactions. It's about creating products that feel intuitive, thoughtful, and just a little easier to use than they were before.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/about"
        class="btn-hover flex items-center justify-center border border-border-secondary bg-[var(--bg-primary)] p-[12px] self-start"
      >
        <span class="flex items-center justify-center px-[4px]">
          <span class="font-mono text-[14px] font-semibold leading-[20px] text-content-primary">
            ABOUT ME
          </span>
        </span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
